  "dcterms:title": "FDA Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS)",
  "dcterms:description": "Quarterly ASCII data extracts from the FDA Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS), a database that supports the FDA's post-marketing safety surveillance program for drug and therapeutic biologic products. Each quarter provides seven relational tables: DEMO (demographic/administrative), DRUG (drug information), REAC (reactions/MedDRA preferred terms), OUTC (patient outcomes), RPSR (report sources), THER (drug therapy start/end dates), and INDI (indications for use). Data span 2004 Q1 through 2026 Q1 (pre-2012 Q4 quarters use the legacy AERS naming).",
